text: Jack Taggart (3 February 1872–1927) was an Irish footballer who played in the Football League for West Bromwich Albion where played in the 1895 FA Cup Final, where they lost 1–0 against Aston Villa. ==References== Category:1872 births Category:1927 deaths Category:Irish association footballers (before 1923) Category:Association football midfielders Category:English Football League players Category:West Bromwich Albion F.C. players Category:Pre-1950 IFA international footballers
